{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἑδραῖος</b>, α, ον, <br /> also ος, ον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 407b, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.288d\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:— <b>sitting, sedentary</b>, of persons or their occupations, ἔργον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 53; οἱ πολλοὶ τῶν τὰς τέχνας ἐχόντων ἑδραῖοί εἰσι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Respublica Lacedaemoniorum” 1.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἑ. ἀρχαί, opposed to στρατεῖαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 407b; ἑ. βίος “Anthologia Graeca” 11.42 (1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Crinagoras Epigrammaticus). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> ἑδραία ῥάχις the horse's back <b>on which the rider sits</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Rhesus” 783. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>steady, steadfast</b>, κάθησ᾽ ἑδραία [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Andr.” 266; δεῖ τὴν γυναῖκα ὥσπερ κύβον ἑδραῖον εἶναι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.288d, compare952d; κύβος -ότατον σῶμα 5th-4th c.BC: Timaeus Locrus Philosophus 98c; ἑ. βάσεις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 59d; ἑδραιότατον στοιχεῖον εἶναι τὴν γῆν 1st c.AD(?): Heraclitus “Allegoriae Quaestiones Homericae” 41; ὂν τὸ πάντων -ότατον 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 6.2.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἑ. ὕπνος <b>sound</b> sleep, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιδημίαι” 6.4.15 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of a cup, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 11.496a \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i> in Rhet., <b>firmly based</b>, κατάληξις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demetrius Phalereus Rhetor “Demetrius on Style” 19, compare 3rd c.AD: Longinus Rhetor 40.4\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> -αίως <b>firmly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Athenaeus Mechanicus 36.10, 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 3.14.5 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; <b>steadily</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD: Proclus Philosophus “Hypotyposis astronomicarum positionum” 3.21. \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>permanently appointed,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PStrassb. 40.11 (6th c.AD). \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1476","accentedUnicode":"ἑδραῖος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1475","matchingForm":"ἔδαφος","stepTransliteration":"edafos","gloss":"ground","_zh_tw_Gloss":"地","_es_Gloss":"suelo ","_zh_Gloss":"地"}],"shortDef":"firm, steadfast","mediumDef":"<b>sedentary;</b>, <i>metaphorically</i> <b>settled, steady, firm, steadfast, constant,</b> <ref='1Co.7.37'>1Cor. 7:37;</ref> 15:58; <ref='Col.1.23'>Col. 1:23</ref>*","stepGloss":"steadfast","stepTransliteration":"hedraios","count":3,"_es_Definition":"firme, fijo, estable","_zh_tw_Definition":"穩固的, 堅定的 (林前 7:37, 15:58; 西 1:23)","_zh_Definition":"稳固的, 坚定的 (林前 7:37, 15:58; 西 1:23)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"vững vàng","_zh_tw_Gloss":"定, 堅定","_es_Gloss":"firme ","_zh_Gloss":"定, 坚定"}]}